summary:
The Security Council,

Reaffirming resolutions 864 (1993) and others, 
Recalling its President's statement of 28 March 2002, 
Reaffirming commitment to Angola's sovereignty and territorial integrity, 
Expressing concern on humanitarian effects on civilians, 
Welcoming the 4 April 2002 ceasefire agreement, 

1. Awaits additional report from monitoring mechanism; 
2. Will consider this report; 
3. Extends monitoring mechanism's mandate for six months until 19 October 2002; 
4. Requests a detailed action plan from monitoring mechanism within 30 days; 
5. Requests periodic reports and a further report by 15 October 2002; 
6. Requests Secretary-General to appoint four experts to monitoring mechanism; 
7. Requests Committee Chairman to submit report by 19 October 2002; 
8. Calls for States' cooperation with monitoring mechanism; 
9. Remains seized of the matter.
